	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok I got my 4th shawl, and here is a summary of how I got Tanik to spawn 2 times.<br><br>The Death Squad and Tanik spawns are not really spawns at all, they are traps...traps that need to be triggered.  <br><br>The first time I triggered Tanik to get my shawl, I was solo (54 Druid).  I used the "item drop method" which was to go to options and change the Fast Drop to confirm.  Then I picked a spot, (facing Kael, I picked the left side of the ramp right on the corner.)  and began trying to drop my foraged food.  When you try to drop it, it gives the confirm box, do not close the confirm box, leave it open and continue clicking around the area you want to check for a trigger, I stood facing to the right (if you were coming from Kael Drakkal) and began clicking and moving my cursor up and down the screen while i slowly turned (to make me face away from Kael).  Every now and then, I would see the message text "You are too far away from You have to trade"  Notice that when you trigger the death spawn, it says "You have been ambushed by Frost Giants"  Well simply put (because no one here really explained)  The trade message you receive is part of the social text that you get when you trigger the spawn, meaning the "You are too far away from [You have] to trade.  This shows that You have is the trigger, and it is actually targetable, a few times while clicking to find the trap which I knew was the Death Squad due to the [You have] reference in the trade message, I ended up in a trade screen with [You have] (note if you complete the trade, you trigger the trap, and lose your foraged food).  It took me triggering the Death Squad and running to Kael zone 9 times, and then finally I got a message that said "You are too far away from You stumble to trade"  The You stumble is Tanik, when you trigger his trap, it says "You stumble over a Coldain covered in snow" (or something like that, but the You stumble part is the first two words and the name of the trap when targeted).  <br><br>I did attempt making /Target You have and /Target You stumble, but those proved to be fruitless, even though I know for a fact that "You Have" can be targeted.<br><br>Total time triggering 2.5 hours, 9 Death Squad triggers, and 1 Tanik trigger<br><br><br>That was the first shawl, then I assisted a necromancer friend of mine get Tanik to spawn again, and this time...it was so much faster.  We had him cast a level 1 pet (no sense in wasing mana since the DS will maul through him anyway)  we parked the pet right in the middle of the ramp to Kael.  I invised up, and he Feigned Death far back on the side of the ramp.  I stood next to the pet and watched the way he turned when my necro friend FD'd.  I would face the same way the pet was standing in front of the pet in the direction he is facing and begin my drop clicking.  I HIGHLY RECOMMEND THIS METHOD.  It was much faster as I had a pretty good idea of where the trigger spot was as opposed to just clicking in every direction a million times.  After either 8 or 9 Death Squad spawns, finally the Tanik "You Stumble" message appeared and we got his note.  This method took about 1.5 hours at most, as you can see this is a big time saver over just doing it solo randomly.<br><br>Notes:<br><br>Seems that Tanik's trigger is 1 out of 10 Death Squad since both times it was 8 or 9 DS before Tanik.<br><br>Tanik Spawned on (facing Kael) the left side of the ramp the first time, and on the right side the second, so it seems his trigger spots are random.<br><br>Keep SoW or Wolf form if you have it up, your going to need it, and head into Kael zone, I noticed that they DS seemed to despawn faster if you zone right away than kite them around or to the Coldain guards.<br><br>Have pacience....when I was doing it alone, I nearly lost my mind working those 2 and a half hours just clicking a piece of fruit on my computer screen, but count the DS spawns, and you will know your that much closer to Tanik's note and your 4th shawl<br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Beebe Lytcaster 51 Necromancer<br>Hiyeedi Fliess 54 Druid<br>~Rallos Zek~</td></tr>
