<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99174537594029></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99174537594029><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=1240&mid=99174537594029 style='color: darkblue;'>How to hit the trigger for Tanik every time...</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=21670><span id=>Alyxz</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 5th 8:49 AM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I found Tanik last night after a good amount of work and time, but my very good friend and I found a method that worked on triggering the trap every single time without much delay....  (other than needing to run and zone to Kael and run back out)<br><br>This requires some guts, a pet class (or as in my case, being able to charm a pet), and most definitely sow and the ability to run to Kael quickly.  Assistance from another is highly recommended, preferably a healer though a monk works very well too...<br><br>This is similar to the method of taking a pet and using /pet guard here (which does work, but takes time).<br><br>Assuming you are the one using the pet,  create a pet and start at the top of the Kael ramp.  Do /pet guard here.  The pet will face the closest threat, either a mob or in this case, the nearest trigger/trap.  Face the pet and begin backing up the way it was facing, and use /pet guard me (or /pet follow me)  to make it follow you a short distance, then issue the /pet guard here command again.  See which way it is facing.  Change your direction again, if needed, to back up in the direction the pet is facing.  I would go about 5 steps or so at a time then give the /pet guard here command.  If you keep doing this, eventually you will hit the trigger.  You may have to go some distance out, or you may hit the trigger fairly quickly.  I found some triggers quite a distance out to the left or the right of the ramp.<br><br>You are most likely to make the Death Squad spawn right on top of you, yes.  RUN (not walk) to Kael zone.  Don't forget to shout Death Squad to Kael along the way to warn of the possible train.  Your pet will do the sacrificial thing and fight to protect you, hopefully giving you a little head start to run away.  To be safe, you probably want to zone to lose the aggro, even though you might be able to get away fast enough to lose the aggro, there's usually someone in the area that will find your Death Squad and train them to Kael after you.  You may not want to zone out of Kael until you're sure the Death Squad is gone.   Sometimes I could make it halfway to Kael and not have them follow me, and they would despawn, but seeing as the Death Squad moves fast and has a big aggro radius (and someone typically finds them and trains them), I quickly learned it was better to zone (died once because of this).  And BTW, do not stop to see if they are following you.  Get most of the way to Kael before you decide to stop and check, if you do at all.<br><br>This is where having a friend to help scout for you comes in handy (or if your friend is the one with the pet, you do the scouting).  Have your friend keep a decent distance away from you and the pet while you are doing this and keep you informed when you hit the trigger, whether the giants are following you, and when they have despawned.  (My friend would tell me "run!" as soon as I hit the trigger, and I found myself with just enough time to get a head start on the Death Squad in most cases).   My friend was a 60 level monk and would also try and aggro the Death Squad off me and then FD.  <br><br>It took a good number of tries, but just when I was about to give up for the night, I got Tanik at last!  Woot!<br><br>This method can definitely be improved, but it worked for me.  BTW, I'm not a true pet class, I'm an enchanter.  My pets were charmed mobs from the area (I liked the snow bunny pet the best, but the poor thing would quickly get squished by the giants, sigh.  The manticore made a good pet too, lasted a good while with the Death Squad).   We were able to trigger the trap every time without fail.  It took about 15 times, sigh, to finally get Tanik.  But, most of the time was just spent in running to Kael and zoning, and running back.  <br><br>Maybe it was my level (56 enchanter) and my low aggro radius, or perhaps the Death Squad takes a second or two to aggro once they spawn, but typically I was able to run away as soon as they spawned, without aggro or with letting the pet aggro and being able to outrun the aggro range.  /shrug.  I was also self-buffed up pretty good, including Rune V, which helped absorb alot of the blows from the Death Squad if they did aggro on me.<br><br>Good luck,<br>Alyxz Starsoul<br>56 Enchanter<br>Red Sky, Bertox<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
